OL,3,C'Cheaper to let police chief retire
OL,4,Cthan suspend him' - commissioner
OL,6,FAsked whether any other senior
OL,7,Fofficers were implicated in the
OL,8,Fallegations made against Mr Anderson,
OL,9,FMr Evison said he was "unable to
OL,10,Fcomment further" due to the ongoing
OL,11,FIOPC investigation.
OL,13,FOne question asked why Mr Evison did
OL,14,Fnot begin the misconduct process while
OL,15,FPaul Anderson was in post.
OL,17,F"To members of the public, it appears
OL,18,Fsuspect ` he was allowed to retire
OL,19,Fwithout facing the question while
OL,20,Fstill in the job," it added.
